 &lt;h1 id=&#34;Complete-Binary-Tree&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Complete-Binary-Tree&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Complete Binary Tree&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Complete Binary Tree&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;Medium&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Medium&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Medium&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Medium&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;problems_problem_content__Xm_eO&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;Given a Binary Tree, write a function to check whether the given Binary Tree is Complete Binary Tree or not. A complete binary tree&amp;nbsp;is a binary tree in which every level, except possibly the last, is completely filled, and all nodes should be as much close to left as possible&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Example 1:
Input:&lt;/strong&gt;
       1
      / \
     2   3
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt;
Complete Binary Tree&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example 2:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt;
              1
            /   \
          2      3
           \    /  \
            4  5    6
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt;
Not Complete Binary Tree
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Constraints:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
1&amp;lt;=Number of Node&amp;lt;=100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;0 &amp;lt;= Data of a node &amp;lt;= 10&lt;sup&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:18px&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Task:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
You don&#39;t need to take input. Just complete the function&lt;strong&gt; isCompleteBT() &lt;/strong&gt;that takes root &lt;strong&gt;node &lt;/strong&gt;as a parameter and returns &lt;strong&gt;true, &lt;/strong&gt;if the tree is Complete else returns &lt;strong&gt;false&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
